<parameter name="content"># Fix Import Path Errors

## The Problem
The import statements in your page files have wrong paths. From `client/src/pages/`, the API file is at `../api/axios.js` not `./api/axios.js`.

## Quick Fix - Run These Commands in Terminal:

```bash
cd "/Users/aaryansaroha/Desktop/Projects/Chalchitra Website"

# Fix all pages to use correct import path
sed -i '' "s|from './api/axios'|from '../api/axios'|g" client/src/pages/*.js client/src/contexts/*.js

# Commit and push
git add -A
git commit -m "Fix import paths: use ../api/axios instead of ./api/axios"
git push origin main
```

## Manual Fix - Edit Each File:

For each file in `client/src/pages/` and `client/src/contexts/`, change:
```javascript
// WRONG - causes red error
import api from './api/axios';

// CORRECT
import api from '../api/axios';
```

